Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing a large dialog corpus and examining various linguistic features. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper examines how people in the corpus mention each other and messaging frequency. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing spoken conversations. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also possible as the paper examines personal dialog and speaker attributes. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper presents experiments predicting speaker attributes using various features.
